## Section 12: Known Issues & Deferred Risks

**Source:** `/close-phase` auto-extracts from summary
**Update:** Each `/close-phase` appends; user cleans up resolved entries

```markdown
| ID | Description | Source | Archive Ref | Status |
|----|-------------|--------|-------------|--------|
```

**Constraint:** Table only — no prose. Excluded from line budget.

---

## Section 13: Migration Journal

**Source:** `/close-phase` appends after each completed change
**Update:** Each `/close-phase`

```
### <change-id> completed (<date>)
**Scope**: <1 sentence>
**Output**: <X source files, Y test files>
**Key Decisions**: <bullet list>
**Lessons**: <bullet list>
```

Each entry: 10-20 lines. Total section: grows over time, pruned by moving entries > 3 months old to `archive/MIGRATION_HISTORY.md`.

---

## Excluded Sections (MUST NOT appear in .claude/CLAUDE.md)

These are Aiit toolchain metadata. Claude already perceives them through system prompts and settings.json. Including them wastes context budget on every conversation.

| Excluded | Why |
|----------|-----|
| Role & Level | Onboard config metadata, stored in settings.json |
| Available Commands (`/discover`, `/execute`, etc.) | Aiit slash commands, auto-discovered by Claude |
| Constraints (Gate/TDD/parallel agents) | Aiit runtime rules, enforced by settings.json + hooks |
| Available MCP Servers | MCP tools, auto-discovered by Claude |
| Available Skills | Skills, auto-discovered by Claude |

---

## Generation Algorithm (for /onboard)

```
1. Run detect_ecosystem() → set $LANGUAGE, $FRAMEWORK
2. Run detect_project_type() → match test-strategies/<type>.md
3. Scan specs/prd/ → populate Active Changes table
4. Prompt user: project description (if not auto-detected)
5. Assemble CLAUDE.md from sections 1-13 (excluding "Excluded Sections")
6. Write .claude/CLAUDE.md
7. Report: "CLAUDE.md generated: <N> lines, <N> active changes"
```
